--useView--shrink: 1;"><div class=" useView-module__etopAW__view css-1i8nh5f" style="--useView--gap: 8px;"><div class=" useView-module__etopAW__view css-935ubk"><div class="rendered-markdown"><div class="Markdown-module__KWqogW__markdownTheme"><h1 data-sourcepos="1:1-1:52">Student Performance Analytics &amp; Prediction System</h1>
<h2 data-sourcepos="3:1-3:12">Overview</h2>
<p data-sourcepos="5:1-5:457">This is a comprehensive student performance analytics and prediction system designed for academic institutions. The application enables tracking of student data, course enrollments, grades, and attendance while providing ML-based grade prediction capabilities. Built as a full-stack web application, it features an information-dense dashboard with data visualization components following Material Design principles optimized for academic data presentation.</p>
<h2 data-sourcepos="7:1-7:20">User Preferences</h2>
<p data-sourcepos="9:1-9:58">Preferred communication style: Simple, everyday language.</p>
<h2 data-sourcepos="11:1-11:23">System Architecture</h2>
<h3 data-sourcepos="13:1-13:26">Frontend Architecture</h3>
<p data-sourcepos="15:1-15:94"><strong data-sourcepos="15:1-15:14">Framework</strong>: React 18 with TypeScript, using Vite as the build tool and development server.</p>
<p data-sourcepos="17:1-17:273"><strong data-sourcepos="17:1-17:24">UI Component System</strong>: Shadcn/ui component library built on Radix UI primitives, providing accessible, customizable components with a "New York" style variant. The design system implements Material Design principles focused on data visualization and information clarity.</p>
<p data-sourcepos="19:1-19:258"><strong data-sourcepos="19:1-19:12">Styling</strong>: Tailwind CSS with custom design tokens defined through CSS variables. The theme supports light/dark modes with comprehensive color schemes for charts, UI elements, and semantic colors. Typography uses Inter font family loaded from Google Fonts.</p>
<p data-sourcepos="21:1-21:23"><strong data-sourcepos="21:1-21:21">State Management</strong>:</p>
<ul data-sourcepos="22:1-24:64">
<li data-sourcepos="22:1-22:134">TanStack Query (React Query) for server state management with configured defaults (no refetch on window focus, infinite stale time)</li>
<li data-sourcepos="23:1-23:50">React Context for theme state (light/dark mode)</li>
<li data-sourcepos="24:1-24:64">React Hook Form with Zod validation for form state management</li>
</ul>
<p data-sourcepos="26:1-26:98"><strong data-sourcepos="26:1-26:12">Routing</strong>: Wouter for client-side routing, providing a lightweight alternative to React Router.</p>
<p data-sourcepos="28:1-28:138"><strong data-sourcepos="28:1-28:23">Data Visualization</strong>: Recharts library for rendering charts (line charts, bar charts, pie charts) on the dashboard and analytics pages.</p>
<h3 data-sourcepos="30:1-30:25">Backend Architecture</h3>
<p data-sourcepos="32:1-32:48"><strong data-sourcepos="32:1-32:12">Runtime</strong>: Node.js with Express.js framework.</p>
<p data-sourcepos="34:1-34:31"><strong data-sourcepos="34:1-34:30">Development vs Production</strong>:</p>
<ul data-sourcepos="35:1-37:82">
<li data-sourcepos="35:1-35:85">Development mode uses Vite dev server with HMR (Hot Module Replacement) middleware</li>
<li data-sourcepos="36:1-36:73">Production mode serves pre-built static assets from the dist directory</li>
<li data-sourcepos="37:1-37:82">Separate entry points (<code class="css-a9lso5">index-dev.ts</code> and <code class="css-a9lso5">index-prod.ts</code>) for each environment</li>
</ul>
<p data-sourcepos="39:1-39:76"><strong data-sourcepos="39:1-39:15">API Design</strong>: RESTful API structure with endpoints organized by resource:</p>
<ul data-sourcepos="40:1-46:57">
<li data-sourcepos="40:1-40:44"><code class="css-a9lso5">/api/students</code> - Student CRUD operations</li>
<li data-sourcepos="41:1-41:37"><code class="css-a9lso5">/api/courses</code> - Course management</li>
<li data-sourcepos="42:1-42:50"><code class="css-a9lso5">/api/enrollments</code> - Course enrollment tracking</li>
<li data-sourcepos="43:1-43:48"><code class="css-a9lso5">/api/grades</code> - Grade recording and retrieval</li>
<li data-sourcepos="44:1-44:42"><code class="css-a9lso5">/api/attendance</code> - Attendance tracking</li>
<li data-sourcepos="45:1-45:50"><code class="css-a9lso5">/api/predictions</code> - ML-based grade predictions</li>
<li data-sourcepos="46:1-46:57"><code class="css-a9lso5">/api/analytics/dashboard</code> - Aggregated analytics data</li>
</ul>
<p data-sourcepos="48:1-48:31"><strong data-sourcepos="48:1-48:30">Request/Response Handling</strong>:</p>
<ul data-sourcepos="49:1-51:52">
<li data-sourcepos="49:1-49:72">JSON body parsing with raw body preservation for webhook verification</li>
<li data-sourcepos="50:1-50:70">Request logging middleware tracking response times and status codes</li>
<li data-sourcepos="51:1-51:52">Error handling with appropriate HTTP status codes</li>
</ul>
<p data-sourcepos="53:1-53:150"><strong data-sourcepos="53:1-53:24">Storage Abstraction</strong>: Interface-based storage layer (<code class="css-a9lso5">IStorage</code>) enabling flexible data persistence implementation (in-memory or database-backed).</p>
<h3 data-sourcepos="55:1-55:26">Database Architecture</h3>
<p data-sourcepos="57:1-57:75"><strong data-sourcepos="57:1-57:8">ORM</strong>: Drizzle ORM configured for PostgreSQL with schema-first approach.</p>
<p data-sourcepos="59:1-59:100"><strong data-sourcepos="59:1-59:22">Database Provider</strong>: Neon Serverless PostgreSQL (based on <code class="css-a9lso5">@neondatabase/serverless</code> dependency).</p>
<p data-sourcepos="61:1-61:19"><strong data-sourcepos="61:1-61:18">Schema Design</strong>:</p>
<p data-sourcepos="63:1-63:66">The database implements a relational structure for academic data:</p>
<ul data-sourcepos="65:1-70:133">
<li data-sourcepos="65:1-65:117"><strong data-sourcepos="65:3-65:21">Students Table</strong>: Core student information including personal details, enrollment date, major, and academic year</li>
<li data-sourcepos="66:1-66:113"><strong data-sourcepos="66:3-66:20">Courses Table</strong>: Course catalog with course codes, credits, department, semester, and instructor information</li>
<li data-sourcepos="67:1-67:96"><strong data-sourcepos="67:3-67:24">Enrollments Table</strong>: Junction table linking students to courses (many-to-many relationship)</li>
<li data-sourcepos="68:1-68:106"><strong data-sourcepos="68:3-68:19">Grades Table</strong>: Individual assignment/exam scores with type classification, weighting, and max scores</li>
<li data-sourcepos="69:1-69:110"><strong data-sourcepos="69:3-69:23">Attendance Table</strong>: Daily attendance records with status (Present/Absent/Late/Excused) and optional notes</li>
<li data-sourcepos="70:1-70:133"><strong data-sourcepos="70:3-70:24">Predictions Table</strong>: ML model predictions storing predicted grades, confidence levels, contributing factors, and recommendations</li>
</ul>
<p data-sourcepos="72:1-72:167"><strong data-sourcepos="72:1-72:22">Schema Validation</strong>: Drizzle-zod integration generates Zod schemas from database schema definitions, ensuring type-safe validation throughout the application stack.</p>
<p data-sourcepos="74:1-74:126"><strong data-sourcepos="74:1-74:23">Migration Strategy</strong>: Drizzle Kit handles schema migrations with configuration pointing to <code class="css-a9lso5">./migrations</code> output directory.</p>
<h3 data-sourcepos="76:1-76:35">Authentication &amp; Authorization</h3>
<p data-sourcepos="78:1-78:233">Currently not implemented - the application appears to be designed for internal institutional use without user authentication. Future implementation would likely require session-based or JWT authentication given the Express backend.</p>
<h3 data-sourcepos="80:1-80:18">Design System</h3>
<p data-sourcepos="82:1-82:144"><strong data-sourcepos="82:1-82:21">Design Framework</strong>: Material Design variant optimized for data-heavy academic applications, prioritizing information clarity over decoration.</p>
<p data-sourcepos="84:1-84:24"><strong data-sourcepos="84:1-84:23">Component Patterns</strong>:</p>
<ul data-sourcepos="85:1-89:57">
<li data-sourcepos="85:1-85:67">Consistent spacing system using Tailwind units (4, 6, 8, 12, 16)</li>
<li data-sourcepos="86:1-86:35">12-column responsive grid layout</li>
<li data-sourcepos="87:1-87:41">Fixed sidebar navigation (16rem width)</li>
<li data-sourcepos="88:1-88:60">Maximum content width (max-w-7xl) for optimal readability</li>
<li data-sourcepos="89:1-89:57">Responsive breakpoints for mobile/tablet/desktop views</li>
</ul>
<p data-sourcepos="91:1-91:22"><strong data-sourcepos="91:1-91:21">Typography Scale</strong>:</p>
<ul data-sourcepos="92:1-97:40">
<li data-sourcepos="92:1-92:35">Page headers: text-3xl font-bold</li>
<li data-sourcepos="93:1-93:44">Section headers: text-2xl font-semibold</li>
<li data-sourcepos="94:1-94:37">Subsections: text-lg font-semibold</li>
<li data-sourcepos="95:1-95:35">Body text: text-base font-normal</li>
<li data-sourcepos="96:1-96:35">Data points: text-sm font-medium</li>
<li data-sourcepos="97:1-97:40">Labels: text-xs font-medium uppercase</li>
</ul>
<p data-sourcepos="99:1-99:207"><strong data-sourcepos="99:1-99:17">Color System</strong>: HSL-based color tokens with semantic naming (primary, secondary, muted, accent, destructive) supporting theme switching. Chart colors defined separately for data visualization consistency.</p>

</ul>
